BLOOMING GROVE WIND ENERGY CENTER LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Blooming Grove Wind Energy Center LLC ("Blooming Grove") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from a wind generation facility located in McLean County, Illinois. Blooming Grove is interconnected to the transmission system owned by Commonwealth Edison Company and operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Blooming Grove's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Blooming Grove facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Blooming Grove's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Blooming Grove shall be subject to Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff.
REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
Total Revenue Requirement:
The Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement is: $1,578,892.08 The Monthly Revenue Requirement is: $131,574.34 (Based on Fixed Annual Revenue Requirement divided by 12)
